{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a010","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCTESTCD | Subject Characteristic Short Name | Char | (SCTESTCD) | Topic | Short name of the measurement, test, or examination described in SCTEST. It can be used as a column name when converting a dataset from a vertical to a horizontal format. The value in SCTEST cannot be longer than 8 characters, nor can it start with a number (e.g., \"TEST\" is not valid). SCTESTCD cannot contain other than letters, numbers, or underscores. Example: \"CAGENHAB\", \"CMHABX\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a011","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCTEST | Subject Characteristic | Char | (SCTEST) | Synonym Qualifier | Verbatim name of the test or examination used to obtain the measurement or finding. The value in SCTEST cannot be longer than 40 characters. Examples: \"Marital Status\", \"National Origin\". | Req |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a012","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCCAT | Category for Subject Characteristic | Char | | Grouping Qualifier | Used to define a category of related records. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a013","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCSCAT | Subcategory for Subject Characteristic | Char | * | Grouping Qualifier | A further categorization of the subject characteristic. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
