{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a016","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCSTRESC | Character Result/Finding in Std Format | Char | | Result Qualifier | Contains the result value for all findings copied or derived from SCORRES, in a standard format or standard units. SCSTRESC should store all results of findings copied or derived from SCORRES in numeric format in numeric format in SCSTRESN. For example, if a test results \"NONE\", \"NEG\", and \"NEGATIVE\" in SCORRES and these result effectively have the same meaning, they could be represented in standard format in SCSTRESC as \"NEGATIVE\". | Exp |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a017","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCSTRESN | Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units | Num | | Result Qualifier | Used for continuous numeric results of findings in standard format; copied in numeric format from SCSTRESN. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a018","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"middle","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCSTRESU | Standardized Units | Char | (UNIT) | Variable Qualifier | Standardized unit used for SCSTRESC or SCSTRESN. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a019","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCSTAT | Completion Status | Char | (ND) | Record Qualifier | Used to indicate that the measurement was not done. Should be null if a result exists in SCORRES. | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id":"ig34_p0340_a020","source":"SDTMIG_v3.4","page":340,"page_region":"bottom","parent_section":"§6.3.10 Subject Characteristics (SC)","atom_type":"TABLE_ROW","verbatim":"| SCREASND | Reason Not Performed | Char | | Record Qualifier | Describes why the observation has no result. Example: \"Subject refused\". Used in conjunction with SCSTAT. When value is \"NOT DONE\". | Perm |","heading_level":null,"sibling_index":null,"figure_ref":null,"cross_refs":[],"extracted_by":{"subagent_type":"oh-my-claudecode:writer","prompt_version":"P0_writer_pdf_v1.3","ts":"2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
